/* D-PARSE-DEEP-NEST-RECURSION-MEMORY (plan 24 Stage 4b) end-to-end witness for
 * the now-iterative HIR->MIR STATEMENT lowerer. The control-flow statement arms
 * in src/mir/lowering/hir_to_mir.cpp (Block's child list, IfStmt's then/else,
 * While/DoWhile/For bodies, LabelStmt, SwitchStmt arms) are now multi-phase
 * frames on an explicit `StmtFrame` WORK-STACK DRIVER (`lowerStmt`): a control-
 * flow statement mints its blocks + emits its branches at the right phases while
 * its sub-statements RE-ENTER the driver, so a deeply-nested statement nest
 * lowers HIR->MIR with FLAT O(1) host-stack cost per nesting level instead of one
 * host-recursion frame per level. (The EXPRESSION lowering inside each statement
 * -- the `if` conditions here -- already flattens via the runExprDriver work-
 * stack.)
 *
 * This program is a 600-level nest `{ if (t()) { { if (t()) { ... r = 42; } } } }`
 * -- each level combines the Block child-list arm and the IfStmt then-arm (~2-3
 * recursive `lowerStmt` frames per level, ~1500 frames deep), exactly the axis
 * the work-stack flattening removes. `t` is an un-inlined identity returning 1,
 * so the optimizer cannot fold the conditions away and the full nested-diamond
 * CFG survives to MIR; every condition is runtime-true, so control descends the
 * ENTIRE then-spine to the innermost `r = 42;` -> the program returns 42.
 *
 * MISCOMPILE-SENSITIVE: `r` is initialized to 0 and only the innermost (deepest)
 * statement sets it to 42. A statement-frame phase bug that took a wrong CondBr
 * edge (false instead of true), dropped/duplicated a diamond, opened the wrong
 * block for a sub-statement, or mis-ordered a Store/Br would skip the deep
 * `r = 42;` assignment -> return the initial 0, not 42.
 *
 * OUTPUT-IDENTITY against the prior recursive lowerer is enforced by the full
 * ctest suite (the byte-identical MIR control-flow block/branch goldens in
 * tests/mir/test_mir_lowering_c_subset.cpp, plus the SF-4 strict differential pin
 * IterativeDeepIfNestLowersFlatAndByteIdentical, which pins the exact deep
 * block-id + CondBr-successor sequence on the test's stack and is red-on-disable
 * to a swapped successor); this example adds the deep-flatten + real-codegen RUN
 * witness for the statement lowerer. The optimizedPipelines arm proves the
 * lowered MIR survives the full release pipeline (the baseline arm is the real-
 * codegen witness). arm64 runs under qemu; macho on the macos-latest leg. */
